{
  "text": "It is noteworthy that crustal underplating or the presence of high-velocity lower crust is not unequivocally documented for modern collisional orogens. For example, the velocity structure of the Altiplano crust, where crustal thickness is 60-65 km, is more consistent with felsic composition than the presence of underplated mantle derived material or magmatic intrusions from the mantle [CITATION_1] .",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "129509706"
